HEADWORD: Cynthia
<hw>Cynthia</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Classical mythology)</fld> <def>the
virgin goddess of the hunt and the moon; daughter of Leto and twin
sister of Apollo; identified with Roman Diana.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Artemis.</syn>⟦br⟧
